WEBVTT

00:02.742 --> 00:04.775
It feels like it
wasn't that long ago

00:04.777 --> 00:07.044
we were here doing
this for Halley.

00:07.046 --> 00:09.580
'Cause it wasn't.

00:09.582 --> 00:11.482
Which reminds me,
before we leave,

00:11.484 --> 00:13.617
let's get you a vasectomy.

00:13.619 --> 00:18.389
Oh, that's sweet, but
today is all about you.

00:20.092 --> 00:23.027
So, you two ready to find
out the sex of this baby?

00:23.029 --> 00:24.295
Yeah.
Absolutely.

00:24.297 --> 00:25.763
Is Halley hoping

00:25.765 --> 00:27.565
for a little brother
or a little sister?

00:27.567 --> 00:28.899
Well, she's nine months old,

00:28.901 --> 00:32.970
so unless it jingles or is
in my bra, she doesn't care.

00:32.972 --> 00:36.340
And how about you two?

00:36.342 --> 00:39.577
You know, for the first one,
we really wanted a girl,

00:39.579 --> 00:42.279
but this time around, we
don't have a preference.

00:42.281 --> 00:45.349
Yeah. Boy, girl,
as long as it's healthy.

00:45.351 --> 00:47.485
Well, it's a boy.

00:47.487 --> 00:49.253
(heartbeat pulsing)

00:49.255 --> 00:52.022
Oh.
Oh.

00:52.024 --> 00:55.593
Come on, you can't
really be disappointed.

00:55.595 --> 00:57.595
Hey, I barely know
how to be a man myself.

00:57.597 --> 00:59.597
Now I have
to teach someone?

00:59.599 --> 01:03.634
As the saying goes,
“Those who can't do, teach”"

01:04.670 --> 01:06.704
Don't you want a little
version of Howard?

01:06.706 --> 01:10.040
I already have a little
version of Howard.

01:10.977 --> 01:12.610
Now I'm having a son?

01:12.612 --> 01:15.412
I'll have to teach him
how to play sports,

01:15.414 --> 01:17.882
and-and watch sports

01:17.884 --> 01:20.851
and-and-and-and-and-and...

01:20.853 --> 01:24.021
He just ran out of man things.
He's in trouble.

01:26.125 --> 01:27.992
It's okay. We're
all here to help.

01:27.994 --> 01:31.562
Yes. And this baby will have
plenty of manly role models.

01:31.564 --> 01:33.898
Now, I'm certain that whatever
Bernadette can't teach him,

01:33.900 --> 01:35.165
Penny can.

01:36.502 --> 01:38.602
Uh, she can pee into a bottle.

01:38.604 --> 01:39.670
Mm-hmm.

01:39.672 --> 01:41.906
Anything with a neck
wider than a nickel.

01:43.843 --> 01:47.278
Howie, there's a lot of amazing
things you can teach a son.

01:47.280 --> 01:50.548
Yeah. You do always know how
to pick just the right antacid.

01:50.550 --> 01:53.551
I don't know if
I can teach that.

01:53.553 --> 01:56.020
It's just something
I was born with.

01:56.022 --> 01:58.055
Come on. You can build things.

01:58.057 --> 01:59.590
You were an astronaut.

01:59.592 --> 02:01.058
That's true.

02:01.060 --> 02:03.394
You know, as a kid,
I used to make model rockets.

02:03.396 --> 02:05.229
That'd be pretty cool
to do with a son.

02:05.231 --> 02:07.865
Model rockets. Finally,
something interesting.

02:07.867 --> 02:11.135
What is your preferred
mode of recovery?

02:11.137 --> 02:13.370
Sheldon, we're helping
our friends.

02:13.372 --> 02:16.607
And we got to model
rockets, yeah?

02:16.609 --> 02:19.810
It was a tedious road,
but well worth the effort.

02:19.812 --> 02:22.479
- So, have you thought of any names?
- Amy.

02:22.481 --> 02:23.647
We finally got
to model rockets.

02:23.649 --> 02:25.082
Why are you
turning back?

02:26.419 --> 02:29.820
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

02:29.822 --> 02:33.424
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

02:33.426 --> 02:34.959
♪ The Earth began to cool ♪

02:34.961 --> 02:37.895
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

02:37.897 --> 02:40.197
♪ We built the Wall ♪
♪ <i>We built the pyramids</i> ♪

02:40.199 --> 02:42.800
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

02:42.802 --> 02:44.735
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

02:44.737 --> 02:45.770
♪ <i>Bang!</i> ♪

02:45.771 --> 02:49.771
