10:18.177 --> 10:19.243
Well, that's perfect.

10:19.245 --> 10:21.211
I mean, the one thing
I thought I could

10:21.213 --> 10:23.948
do with my son,
I can't even do that right.

10:23.950 --> 10:27.418
Well, if you want to see it
again, I got it on video.

10:27.420 --> 10:30.254
Looks pretty cool
in slow motion.

10:30.256 --> 10:31.956
Thank you for
your support.

10:31.958 --> 10:34.224
You're welcome.
I was being sarcastic.

10:34.226 --> 10:35.859
How dare you!

10:37.930 --> 10:40.197
Sheldon, what am I
gonna do?

10:40.199 --> 10:44.268
I mean, what do I know
about raising a boy?

10:44.270 --> 10:48.205
What do you know
about raising a girl?

10:49.542 --> 10:52.309
Oh, my God, you're right.

10:52.311 --> 10:55.512
Well, I don't know if
that was sarcasm or not.

10:55.514 --> 10:58.949
So, either you're welcome,
or hey!

11:03.589 --> 11:05.723
(phone chimes)

11:07.493 --> 11:09.293
Leonard, did you really
just text me from the couch

11:09.295 --> 11:11.895
to put extra mustard
on your sandwich?

11:11.897 --> 11:15.032
I was worried you might not
check your e-mail.

11:17.536 --> 11:18.535
(phone chimes)

11:18.537 --> 11:20.671
I swear to God,
I will throw this out.

11:20.673 --> 11:22.406
That one was not me.

11:22.408 --> 11:24.241
Oh, wait, it was just your mom.

11:24.243 --> 11:25.876
My mother's texting you?

11:25.878 --> 11:27.978
Yeah. We've been talking
a lot lately.

11:27.980 --> 11:30.047
Why?

11:30.049 --> 11:33.951
She sick of talking to
the magic mirror on the wall?

11:33.953 --> 11:36.320
No, I think she's lonely.

11:36.322 --> 11:37.955
She's been reaching out.

11:37.957 --> 11:41.392
Okay, just be careful.

11:41.394 --> 11:42.993
You think you're
getting close to her,

11:42.995 --> 11:45.429
and the next thing you know,
you're featured in a book

11:45.431 --> 11:50.067
called <i>He's Doing It On Purpose:</i>
<i>Raising a Teenage Bed-Wetter.</i>

11:50.069 --> 11:52.002
No, it's not like that.

11:52.004 --> 11:54.204
You know, she's been
opening up about her life,

11:54.206 --> 11:56.807
and she's actually been
really supportive about mine.

11:56.809 --> 11:58.208
Really?
Yeah.

11:58.210 --> 11:59.443
I've been telling her
about my job,

11:59.445 --> 12:01.512
and she said
she was proud of me.

12:01.514 --> 12:04.882
Well, that's great.

12:05.951 --> 12:08.952
Never told me
she was proud of me.

12:10.489 --> 12:14.124
Even when I stayed dry
for a whole month.

12:14.126 --> 12:17.261
Do you not want me
to be friends with your mom?

12:17.263 --> 12:18.896
Well, let's be clear.

12:18.898 --> 12:21.965
I-I married you to hurt her.

12:24.603 --> 12:26.904
You're kind of ruining it.

12:29.275 --> 12:32.676
Reason number 13
to feel good:

12:32.678 --> 12:34.912
as a launch, it was bad,

12:34.914 --> 12:37.815
but as an explosion,
it was glorious.

12:39.452 --> 12:40.884
Reason 14:

12:40.886 --> 12:43.620
you still have
all your fingers,

12:43.622 --> 12:46.723
and boys prefer
a dad with fingers.

12:46.725 --> 12:48.125
Thanks for trying,

12:48.127 --> 12:50.427
but you're not gonna be able
to cheer me up.

12:50.429 --> 12:52.496
Well, how about
this, then?

12:52.498 --> 12:54.231
You quit your whining
before I give you

12:54.233 --> 12:56.300
something to cry
about, young man.

12:56.302 --> 12:58.435
What?

12:58.437 --> 13:02.406
Those are comforting words
my father would often say.

13:02.408 --> 13:04.241
Did it help?

13:04.243 --> 13:06.176
I turned out great.

13:06.178 --> 13:07.678
You tell me.

13:07.680 --> 13:10.280
Let's get going.

13:10.282 --> 13:13.150
Are you gonna be this
mopey all the way home?

13:13.152 --> 13:14.685
I don't know, maybe.

13:14.687 --> 13:16.353
There any chance
you'd be cheered up

13:16.355 --> 13:18.622
by an amazing
trigonometry riddle?

13:20.259 --> 13:21.925
Well, if you can't
answer that,

13:21.927 --> 13:24.027
there's no way you're
gonna get this riddle.

13:30.936 --> 13:33.770
Oh, hey, hey,
what do you think?

13:33.772 --> 13:36.140
Just because it's a boy,
I don't think you need to

13:36.142 --> 13:38.609
put a picture of
genitals on his shirt.

13:38.611 --> 13:42.379
But that's a baseball bat
with two little baseballs.

13:42.381 --> 13:45.149
Okay, and now I see it.

13:46.886 --> 13:49.286
So, you know,
I understand why

13:49.288 --> 13:51.255
Howard is nervous
about having a son,

13:51.257 --> 13:53.223
but are you really
upset about it?

13:53.225 --> 13:54.858
No, I'm fine.

13:54.860 --> 13:56.827
It's just, I grew up
with a bunch of brothers,

13:56.829 --> 13:59.496
so I thought it'd be nice
for Halley to have a sister.

13:59.498 --> 14:00.631
Is that wrong?

14:00.633 --> 14:02.566
Of course it's wrong.

14:02.568 --> 14:04.101
You don't know what this
little boy's gonna be like.

14:04.103 --> 14:06.503
Maybe he'll be rough and tumble,

14:06.505 --> 14:08.805
or maybe he'll be sweet
and sensitive,

14:08.807 --> 14:12.409
or maybe he'll be
all those things, like me.

14:14.513 --> 14:16.480
You're rough
and tumble?

14:18.083 --> 14:21.151
You bet I am, bitch.

14:22.288 --> 14:26.823
But I'm also sensitive
and regret saying that.

14:29.695 --> 14:31.128
(knock on door)

14:31.130 --> 14:33.263
Hey.
Hello.

14:33.265 --> 14:35.732
You got a sec?

14:35.734 --> 14:36.700
Sure. What's up?

14:36.702 --> 14:39.036
Penny's been talking
to my mother

14:39.038 --> 14:42.172
like they're best friends, and
it's kind of freaking me out.

14:42.174 --> 14:44.775
Okay...

14:44.777 --> 14:48.946
I'm pretty sure
they're not best friends.

14:51.317 --> 14:54.451
'Cause you can only have
one best friend.

14:56.021 --> 14:59.389
And Penny has that,
and (clicks tongue) it's me.

15:01.060 --> 15:03.493
Oh, really? Is she FaceTiming
with you right now?

15:03.495 --> 15:05.429
Because she's FaceTiming
with my mom, and believe me,

15:05.431 --> 15:08.899
that is not a face
you want to spend time with.

15:08.901 --> 15:12.569
Hmm. Well, I have been
pretty busy lately.

15:12.571 --> 15:14.638
Maybe I've been
neglecting our friendship.

15:14.640 --> 15:16.106
Penny knows I have
a complicated relationship

15:16.108 --> 15:17.874
with my mother;
it's like she doesn't even care.

15:17.876 --> 15:19.443
And with everything
going on at the lab

15:19.445 --> 15:20.711
and planning the wedding,

15:20.713 --> 15:23.547
I just, I have
so little free time.

15:23.549 --> 15:26.350
Penny doesn't know how
manipulative my mother can be.

15:26.352 --> 15:27.651
Did you know
there's such a thing as

15:27.653 --> 15:29.519
reverse, reverse,
reverse psychology?

15:29.521 --> 15:32.856
Because... there is.

15:32.858 --> 15:34.358
I mean, she must feel
so abandoned.

15:34.360 --> 15:36.226
She's used to me
being there all the time,

15:36.228 --> 15:37.628
but now I have my own life,

15:37.630 --> 15:39.696
and she's just gonna
have to accept it.

15:39.698 --> 15:42.499
And why is my mom
proud of Penny and not me?

15:42.501 --> 15:44.568
I mean, the real question is:
why is Penny so afraid of me

15:44.570 --> 15:45.669
growing as a person?

15:45.671 --> 15:46.870
I'm good at stuff, too!

15:46.872 --> 15:49.339
I deserve my own life!

15:51.510 --> 15:53.076
Okay, well, thanks.

15:53.078 --> 15:54.645
Good talk.

16:00.619 --> 16:02.452
You know,
studies have shown

16:02.454 --> 16:05.589
that people distracted
by emotional issues

16:05.591 --> 16:07.557
are poor drivers.

16:07.559 --> 16:12.362
What about people distracted
by irritating passengers?

16:13.299 --> 16:14.798
That would be hard to test,

16:14.800 --> 16:17.968
because irritating is
a subjective quality.

16:17.970 --> 16:20.837
Strongly disagree.

16:25.711 --> 16:27.010
Can I drive?

16:27.012 --> 16:28.612
No. (chuckles)

16:28.614 --> 16:29.746
You can't drive.

16:29.748 --> 16:31.815
You don't even have a license.

16:31.817 --> 16:33.016
Actually, I do.

16:33.018 --> 16:36.286
Really? Since when?

16:36.288 --> 16:37.721
Three years ago.

16:37.723 --> 16:40.324
I went on a bit
of a license kick.

16:40.326 --> 16:43.293
I'm also
a commercial fisherman.

16:44.196 --> 16:46.863
Then why don't you ever
drive yourself?

16:46.865 --> 16:48.732
Honestly, I barely
passed my test.

16:48.734 --> 16:50.634
And the one time
I drove on my own,

16:50.636 --> 16:55.205
I made a U-turn, got dizzy,
threw up and walked home.

16:56.442 --> 16:58.342
You really want to drive?

16:58.344 --> 17:00.477
It seems like
the perfect time.

17:00.479 --> 17:03.213
The roads are straight,
there's no one around,

17:03.215 --> 17:06.483
and you don't seem to care
if you live or die.

17:06.484 --> 17:10.020
Live, Sheldon.
I want to live.

17:10.021 --> 17:11.688
That makes things
a little trickier,

17:11.690 --> 17:13.323
but I'll do my best.

17:15.661 --> 17:17.361
(line ringing)

17:17.363 --> 17:18.395
BEVERLY:
Hi, Pen...

17:18.396 --> 17:21.164
Oh, hello, Leonard.

17:22.835 --> 17:24.166
Hello, Mother. How are you?

17:24.169 --> 17:26.303
Fine. And you?
I'm great.

17:26.305 --> 17:28.472
Well, it's been lovely
catching up.

17:28.473 --> 17:31.108
Wait. Hang on.
We need to talk.

17:31.110 --> 17:33.877
Oh, brother.

17:33.879 --> 17:37.614
I want to know,
why aren't you proud of me?

17:37.616 --> 17:39.816
Well, isn't the real question,

17:39.818 --> 17:41.985
“Why aren't you proud
of yourself?”

17:41.987 --> 17:47.557
No, that is <i>a</i> question--
and I ask it a lot--

17:47.559 --> 17:49.860
but let's stick
with the one I asked you.

17:49.862 --> 17:52.629
But why do you think
I'm not proud of you?

17:52.631 --> 17:55.065
Because you never say it.

17:55.067 --> 17:56.767
But two days into
chatting with Penny,

17:56.769 --> 17:59.136
and you can't stop
telling her how great she is.

17:59.138 --> 18:00.370
She is great.

18:00.372 --> 18:03.440
Honestly, of all
of my children's spouses,

18:03.442 --> 18:05.942
she's the one
that I'm most impressed by.

18:05.944 --> 18:07.944
Seriously?

18:07.946 --> 18:09.045
Yes.

18:09.047 --> 18:11.448
She's confident,
she's thoughtful,

18:11.450 --> 18:13.650
and she never complained
about you once.

18:13.652 --> 18:16.987
I know what kind of strength
that takes.

18:16.989 --> 18:20.424
So, Penny's your favorite?

18:20.426 --> 18:22.893
I suppose she is.

18:22.895 --> 18:27.297
You married well, Leonard,
and for that I am proud of you.

18:29.968 --> 18:32.536
I don't... I don't...
I don't know what to say.

18:32.538 --> 18:36.506
I'm also proud of how hard
you're trying not to cry.

18:38.343 --> 18:39.676
(choked up):
Thank you.

18:39.678 --> 18:41.478
Would you like to hang up now?

18:41.480 --> 18:43.180
Yeah, here it comes.

18:50.456 --> 18:52.622
Your hands are at
10:00 and 2:00.

18:52.624 --> 18:55.559
Good.
Steady on the gas.

18:55.561 --> 18:57.360
Okay.

18:57.362 --> 19:01.031
Now you're gonna want
to slowly switch lanes.

19:01.033 --> 19:02.032
Why?

19:02.034 --> 19:03.900
Because there are only two,

19:03.902 --> 19:06.336
and you're not
in either of them.

19:10.542 --> 19:12.642
Attaboy. Well done!

19:12.644 --> 19:13.944
Thank you.

19:13.946 --> 19:16.446
The last time I drove,
I was terrified,

19:16.448 --> 19:18.048
but this is fun.

19:18.050 --> 19:19.916
You're doing great.

19:19.918 --> 19:22.085
You're a good teacher.

19:24.623 --> 19:28.358
Your son is going to be lucky
to have you as a father.

19:28.360 --> 19:30.594
Thanks.

19:33.398 --> 19:37.267
Do you think I could try
going a little faster?

19:37.269 --> 19:38.768
Go for it, champ.

19:38.770 --> 19:40.837
Ow.

19:40.839 --> 19:42.272
Sorry.

19:42.274 --> 19:44.441
Just ease on the gas, and...

19:44.443 --> 19:45.909
(engine revving)
Oh, too much! Too much!

19:45.911 --> 19:48.578
Why was I scared of this?
This is exhilarating!

19:48.580 --> 19:49.946
No, it's not! Slow down!

19:49.948 --> 19:51.848
Don't tell me what to do!
You're not my father!

20:05.455 --> 20:07.488
Do you know how fast
you were going?

20:07.490 --> 20:09.924
112.

20:11.361 --> 20:13.294
Let me see your license.

20:14.864 --> 20:17.331
- Okay, here's the plan.
-No.

20:19.035 --> 20:20.034
Fine.

20:20.036 --> 20:22.103
There you go.

20:24.441 --> 20:27.074
You know what,
you can just keep it.

